 BY BENEDICT NWACHUKWU, ABUJA At last, the National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Caretaker/Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC) and Governor of Yobe State, Mai Mala Buni, has approved the appointment of the partyâ€™s zoning committee for the forthcoming National Convention. The appointment which was contained in a statement by the national secretary, Senator John Akpanudoedehe, shows that the Governor of Kwara State, AbdulRahaman AbdulRazak, is the chairman with the Deputy President of the Senate, Ovie Omo-Agege, as the deputy chairman. Other members are Prof.  Etim Nyong,
Dr. MB Shehu, Comrade Mustapha Salihu, Sen. Teslim Folarin, Alh. Sadeeq Sule-Iko Sami and the Deputy Governor of Anambra State, Dr Nkem Okeke, who will served as the Secretary. The Committee, according to the statement, is expected to submit its report on Monday 7th March, 2022. 